The case we reported was very nervous and exhibited a long-term high-frequency startle response, which disrupted his sleep seriously and decreased treatment compliance.Thus, we report it to provide a different experience for future research and clinical practice.(1) Paroxysmal sympathetic hyperactivity (PSH) mainly occurs in patients with brain injury.14 The patient had no history of brain injury, and his MRI testing result was normal.After he was allowed to sleep on the pillow, the startle response only appeared when he turned over.Although obtaining patients’ information from family members is essential, it might be influenced by family members’ psychological states.
